narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Learned how to make a game with pygame
I became a much better independent programmer
Better time management skills and experience working on a self-motivated project!

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Professor Glenn was a great independent adviser. He was frequently accessible. He gave great feedback and I learned a lot from the project I did with him.
The level of flexibility was great and my advisor was very helpful

Meeting with Dana every week was a privilege! She was extremely supportive and helped me walk through papers when I was confused or stumped. I am extremely honored to have worked with her in my time at Yale!
Very dependent on your advisor. Lol. Find one with grad students that can help you out.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes I highly suggest the senior thesis if you are a cs major seeking to graduate.
It is your senior project for CS you cannot get out of it.
It's required. Don't expect that much support from the department if you pursue your own project. That being said, great opportunity to go all in on a project you've been considering.
Yes, I really enjoyed working on an extended project in a new area of Computer Science and learned a lot
Yes! It's a great, in-depth way of exploring topics in computer science you may have only touched upon briefly in other classes.
You have to take this, probably, if you're looking at this.
